<% provide(:title, 'JSON Encoding Error Demo') %>
<h1>JSON Encoding Error Demo</h1>

<p class="lead">
  Demonstrates how Ruby DI handles probes that capture binary data.
</p>

<div class="panel panel-default">
  <div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title">Background</h4></div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>
      When a DI probe fires on a method, it captures a <strong>snapshot</strong> of local variables
      and arguments. That snapshot is serialized to JSON and sent to Datadog.
    </p>
    <p>
      If the captured data contains non-UTF-8 binary bytes (e.g. from a custom serializer that
      returns raw binary strings), JSON encoding fails. Without error handling, this failure is
      silent: snapshots are dropped, the probe appears healthy, and only telemetry tracks the issue.
    </p>
    <p>
      With proper error handling (dd-trace-rb PR #5448), a JSON encoding failure
      <strong>disables the probe and reports ERROR status</strong> to the Datadog UI.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading"><h4 class="panel-title">How to Test</h4></div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <ol>
      <li>In Datadog, set a <strong>method probe</strong> on <code>BinaryDataModel#process</code></li>
      <li>Wait for the probe to appear as active on <%= link_to "DI Probes", probes_path %></li>
      <li>Click <strong>Normal Operation</strong> below — snapshot captures and serializes successfully</li>
      <li>Click <strong>Trigger JSON Error</strong> — <code>metadata</code> contains binary data, JSON encoding fails, probe is automatically disabled with ERROR status</li>
      <li>Return to <%= link_to "DI Probes", probes_path %> to see the probe status change</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="well">
  <h4>Run the Demo</h4>
  <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
    Both buttons hit <code>BinaryDataModel#process</code>. The difference is whether
    <code>metadata[:trigger_json_error]</code> is set, which causes the serializer to produce
    non-UTF-8 binary data.
  </p>
  <a href="/debugger_test/binary_data" class="btn btn-success" target="_blank">
    <strong>Normal Operation</strong><br>
    <small>Snapshot serializes correctly</small>
  </a>
  <a href="/debugger_test/binary_data?trigger_error=true" class="btn btn-danger" style="margin-left: 10px;" target="_blank">
    <strong>Trigger JSON Error</strong><br>
    <small>Probe will be disabled with ERROR status</small>
  </a>
</div>
